<span id="freeTextContainer3945013122263488861"><b>after:</b> oh dear. oh Aimee. i love you so, have loved you so, continue to love you so, but i am so sorry to say that this book was a bit of a disappointment. it felt... unfinished. hinted at. like an early draft, almost. i know how stunning you can be, and it isn&apos;t that this is <i>bad</i> or anything... it&apos;s just not up to the standard i expected. which is probably partially my fault. probably just like <i>
  <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6566887.The_Ticking_Is_the_Bomb_A_Memoir' title='The Ticking Is the Bomb A Memoir by Nick Flynn' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Ticking Is the Bomb</a>
</i>, just like <i>
  <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5814.Slow_Learner' title='Slow Learner by Thomas Pynchon' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Learners</a>
