<div id="review_2328195550" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2328195550" />
    <a title="JV (semi-hiatus)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus"><img alt="JV (semi-hiatus)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1559624981p2/20906165.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2328195550?book_show_action=true">Mar 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JV (semi-hiatus)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JV (semi-hiatus)" href="/user/show/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus">JV (semi-hiatus)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus?shelf=curiouser-and-curiouser">curiouser-and-curiouser</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20906165-jv-semi-hiatus?shelf=michelin-stars">michelin-stars</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2328195550" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9426971211278575729"><b>Metaphorically decadent, but acridly convoluted.</b><br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7048800.The_Particular_Sadness_of_Lemon_Cake' title='The Particular Sadness of Lemon Cake by Aimee Bender' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Particular Sadness of Lemon Cake</a> is a bizarre novel, but certainly not in a good way. The delectable premise of having a magical gift that can taste people&apos;s hidden emotions is fascinating, but when you infuse other individual&apos;s special &quot;gifts&quot; with a pint of magical realism into the already rich mixture, that&apos;s the time it becomes nauseously perplexing. <br/><br/>Yes, there&apos;s a bitter sadness in this novel, but I&apos;m not emotionally invested in any of the</span>
  <span id="freeText9426971211278575729" style="display:none"><b>Metaphorically decadent, but acridly convoluted.</b><br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7048800.The_Particular_Sadness_of_Lemon_Cake" title="The Particular Sadness of Lemon Cake by Aimee Bender" rel="nofollow noopener">The Particular Sadness of Lemon Cake</a> is a bizarre novel, but certainly not in a good way. The delectable premise of having a magical gift that can taste people's hidden emotions is fascinating, but when you infuse other individual's special "gifts" with a pint of magical realism into the already rich mixture, that's the time it becomes nauseously perplexing. <br /><br />Yes, there's a bitter sadness in this novel, but I'm not emotionally invested in any of the characters. The writing is lush and creative which I truly appreciate. With magical realism in play, Bender might be alluding to various mental health issues, autism, estrangement, phobias, and other genetic oddities (supertasters and hyperosmia).<br /><br />Now, if I may be excused, I would prefer my after-dinner mints rather than this upsetting dessert. <br /> <br /><b>2.5 stars</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="9426971211278575729" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


