        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1359293315" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6741362574038303935">Rose has a special ability: when she eats she can taste the emotions of the person who made the food. There’s more to it than that and this ability starts to define her life, as it forces her to see the world differently to anyone else. It’s a huge burden she must find some way to live with.<br/><br/>Every so often a book comes along that connects in a way very few others ever have. This was one of those books for me. I totally fell in love with Bender’s idiosyncratic writing style. I felt like this book </span>
  <span id="freeText6741362574038303935" style="display:none">Rose has a special ability: when she eats she can taste the emotions of the person who made the food. There’s more to it than that and this ability starts to define her life, as it forces her to see the world differently to anyone else. It’s a huge burden she must find some way to live with.<br /><br />Every so often a book comes along that connects in a way very few others ever have. This was one of those books for me. I totally fell in love with Bender’s idiosyncratic writing style. I felt like this book was written in my blood. I am Rose. I am Joseph. I am their father. I am their grandfather. I am Graham.<br /><br />If anyone wants an insight into what life is like for me, read this book.<br /><br />My mum recommended this book to me. I think she might know me better than I ever thought she might.<br /><br />Either that or she just thought it was a good book. Whatever.</span>
